        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Each <em>cassock of devotion</em> depicts scenes related to the domains of a certain deity. It serves as a religious symbol of that deity, and it doesn't need to be wielded to provide that benefit. You gain a +2 item bonus to Religion checks and a +1 item bonus to the divine skill of the deity to whom the cassock is dedicated.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">F</span> envision</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You gain 1 Focus Point, which you can spend only to cast a cleric domain spell for a domain belonging to the deity the cassock is dedicated to. If you don't spend this Focus Point by the end of this turn, it is lost.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> You are a cleric who worships the deity tied to the cassock.</p>"
